      • getStop

        public org.json.JSONObject getStop(Stop stop)
        Gets the stop data from the RouteMatch server. If the final encoded url is somehow malformed (most likely through a bad stop id) then an empty JSONObject will be returned instead.
        Parameters:
        stop - The stop to get the data for.
        Returns:
        The data as a JSONObject for the pertaining stop.

      • getBuses

        public org.json.JSONObject getBuses(Route route)

        Parameters:
        route - The specific route to be fetched.
        Returns:

      • getLandRoute

        public org.json.JSONObject getLandRoute(Route route)
        Gets the land route (the route the buses will take) of a particular route from the RouteMatch server.
        Parameters:
        route - The route to be fetched.
        Returns:
        The JSONObject pertaining to the specific route's route (what route it will take as a series of latitude and longitude coordinates).
